basics.name: Matt Sheehan
basics.label: Software Developer
basics.summary: Achieve a position that utilizes my experience architecting large software projects, researching and learning technologies that can be applied, and my strong ability to work independently and with teams.

highlights: Lead in the development of the XvWeb client software.
Worked in ASP.NET 5, javascript, and other web technologies.
Developed Windows 8/8.1 metro app for viewing x-rays with image enhancement algorithms and manipulations (gaussian blur, unsharp mask, b/c/g, ...).
Initiated cloud web application with the ability to enhance images with WebGL shaders.
Created the canonical internal javascript library for web applications, including web-components and custom binding tags.
Deployed a distributed system of micro-services for file syncing, program logging, and user auditing.
Programmed in technologies including DirectX, ASP.NET MVC, WebGL, SQLite, and SQL Server.
Performed technical assessments and serviced customer computers.
Disassembled computers, printers, and any other electronics to recycle the individual components.
